Checkout and install a dotfiles repository from a Git URL

Usage:
  coder dotfiles [git_repo_url] [flags]

Get Started:
  - Check out and install a dotfiles repository without prompts:                

      [;m$ coder dotfiles --yes git@github.com:example/dotfiles.git[0m 

Options
  -h, --help  
          help for dotfiles.
          
      --symlink-dir string  
          $$CODER_SYMLINK_DIR
          Specifies the directory for the dotfiles symlink destinations. If
          empty will use $HOME.
          
  -y, --yes  
          Bypass prompts.
